    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Botanically, a berry, more or less globular, within the juicy pulp of which lie the seeds, derived from the deciduous woody vines of the botanical genus Vitis; grapes range in colors from black, purple, reddish, amber, and green. Grapes can be eaten fresh, dried, or fermented to make wine. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
